    "summary": "Troy is an urban planner and is the Founder & Managing Director of Troy Planning + Design with offices in London, Amsterdam and Portland Oregon.\n\nHe has extensive experience in plan-making from the regional scale to street level plans. He is a regular advisor to local governments on strategic planning including large scale developments, the preparation of technical evidence base and masterplanning to support these projects, including infrastructure requirements, environmental capacity and financial viability.\n\nHe is a regular speaker on innovation and digital transformation in the fields of urban planning and urban design including the use of a range of digital planning tools to improve the planning-making and engagement process. His company has recently developed WholePlan an interactive and flexible digital planning tool for the purpose of plan-making and technical analytics, visualizing new developments (including Virtual Reality) and testing the economic viability of development proposals. The model is currently being used to test and inform potential Land Value Capture for funding infrastructure projects through innovative funding mechanisms.\n\nHe is a certified member of the American Institute of Certified Planners (AICP) and is a chartered member of the Royal Town Planning Insitute (MRTPI).",
